<para>OpenLink&#39;s Single-Tier drivers are clientside-only drivers.
 They are developed solely for use on WinNT clients, and they rely upon the database&#39;s native communications layer to establish their connection.
 If you want to use Single-Tier drivers, you must install both the drivers and the database client on your PC.</para><para>Finally, OpenLink urges you to employ Multi-Tier drivers when possible.
 However, Single-Tier drivers are suitable, if you cannot install software to your server.</para><para>See Also: Lite </para></section></docbook>